<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They recently rekindled their romance after over a year apart following a cheating scandal. </p>

<p>And Khloe Kardashian looked comfortable alongside her on-again flame Tristan Thompson as they stopped by a cosmetic center in Beverly Hills on Friday. </p>

<p>The couple was joined by the 36-year-old star's Keeping Up With the Kardashians filming crew as they film their show's final season.</p>

<p>Lovebirds: Khloe Kardashian looked comfortable alongside her on-again flame Tristan Thompson as they stopped by a cosmetic center in Beverly Hills on Friday </p>

<p>The Good American founder looked chic as she donned black ankle length leggings and an oversized black Balenciaga button-up shirt that she wore as outerwear. </p>

<p>Khloe teamed the look with black and white sneakers, a white face mask and large square sunglasses. </p>

<p>Meanwhile Tristan looked sporty in grey athletic shorts, Nike socks and sneakers, and a white tee. </p>

<p>He also dutifully wore a white face mask amid the coronavirus pandemic and teamed it with a white cap. </p>

<p>Filming: The couple was joined by the 36-year-old star's Keeping Up With the Kardashians filming crew as they film their show's final season </p>

<p>Covered: Khloe looked chic in a black Balenciaga button-up shirt that she wore as outerwear, as they both donned white face masks amid the pandemic </p>

<p>The pair are rumored to have recently rekindled their romance, but a source recently told Us Weekly she 'doesn't really care' what people think of her love life.  </p>

<p>After a tumultuous on-again-off-again relationship, Khloé and Tristan previously called it quits after his 2019 cheating scandal with Jordyn Woods.</p>

<p>In August, a source told People, 'She loves having him around. He has the best relationship with True, and he has been amazing to Khloé too. They are very much together and Khloé is beyond happy.'</p>

<p>'They have been living in kind of a bubble and Khloé enjoys it,' the source added.</p>

<p>The insider also claimed that she was 'beyond happy' and hoped 'that Tristan has changed.' </p>

<p> Family: The pair are rumored to have recently rekindled their romance, but a source recently told Us Weekly she 'doesn't really care' what people think of her love life, they share two-year-old daughter True</p>

<p> Wow factor: Late last month, Khloe shared a sultry snap of herself rocking the Good American bikini collection</p>

<p> Interesting: Scott took to the comments and wrote that Tristan 'is a lucky man,' seemingly confirming their relationship</p>

<p>Khloé weathered Tristan's first cheating scandal in 2018, two days before she gave birth to True. </p>

<p>Scott Disick also gave his seal of approval late last month as Khloe shared a sultry bikini snap he commented that Tristan 'is a lucky man.' </p>

<p>Earlier this month, Kim dropped the shocking news that her series Keeping Up With The Kardashians will end in 2014 with season 20.  </p>

<p>The iconic reality TV series has followed the lives of the Kardashian-Jenner family - including sisters Kourtney, Kim, and Khloe Kardashian, half sisters Kendall and Kylie Jenner, brother Rob Kardashian, and mother Kris Jenner, spawning over 12 spin-offs. </p>

<p>Coming to an end: KUWTK will end next year after 14 years and 20 seasons on E!</p>

<p>Kim announced the news on her Instagram account on Tuesday, where she wrote in a statement: 'It is with heavy hearts that we've made the difficult decision as a family to say goodbye to Keeping Up with the Kardashians.</p>

<p>'After what will be 14 years, 20 seasons, hundreds of episodes and numerous spin-off shows, we are beyond grateful to all of you who've watched us for all of these years – through the good times, the bad times, the happiness, the tears, and the many relationships and children. We'll forever cherish the wonderful memories and countless people we've met along the way.'</p>

<p>Kim went on to thank everyone who has been a part of the E! reality show over the years, and credited the series with 'changing [her] life forever'.</p>

<p>She added: 'Thank you to the thousands of individuals and businesses that have been a part of this experience and, most importantly, a very special thank you to Ryan Seacrest for believing in us, E! for being our partner, and our production team at Bunim/Murray, who've spent countless hours documenting our lives.</p>
